                <note rend="inline" type="source">123 Stuart, J. Leighton: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-07-01T18:00:00-04:00"
                            >July 1, 1949—6 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>775. Following highest level consideration urtel 1410,<note n="76"
                        xml:id="d916fn76">Dated June 30, noon, <ref target="#pg_766">p.
                        766</ref>.</note> you are instructed under no circumstances to make visit
                    Peiping. Principal reasons for negative decision are those contained urtel.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
